sec.p:
The predicted rating $\hat{r}_{u, i}$ for user $u$ on item $i$ is computed as [1]:
\begin{equation*}
\hat{r}_{u, i}=\frac{\sum_{v \in N_{u}} s(u, v) \cdot r_{v, i}}{\sum_{v \in N_{u}}\verts(u, v)\vert}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}
where $s(u, v)$ is the similarity between users $u$ and $v$, and $N_{u}$ is the set of users similar to $u$.

MF learns latent vectors for users and items. The rating matrix $R$ is approximated as the product of two low-rank matrices [2]:
\begin{equation*}
R \approx P Q^{\top}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}
where $P \in \mathbb{R}^{\vertU\vert \times k}$ and $Q \in \mathbb{R}^{\vertI\vert \times k}$. Each user $u$ and item $i$ has a latent vector $p_{u}$ and $q_{i}$, and the predicted rating is:
\begin{equation*}
\hat{r}_{u, i}=p_{u}^{\top} q_{i}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}

At layer $l$, the embedding of node $u$ is updated by aggregating information from its neighbors [4]:
\begin{equation*}
\begin{aligned}
h_{u}^{(l)}=\sigma & \left(W ^ { (l) } \cdot \operatorname { A G G R E G A T E } \left(\left\{h_{v}^{(l-1)}\right.\right.\right. \\
& \left.\left.: v \in \mathcal{N}(u)\} \cup\left\{h_{u}^{(l-1)}\right\}\right)\right)
\end{aligned}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}
where $W^{(l)}$ is a learnable weight matrix, $\sigma$ is a non-linear activation function, and AGGREGATE can be a mean, sum, or max function.

Each node embedding is updated using the GraphSAGE update rule:
\begin{equation*}
\begin{aligned}
h_{u}^{(l)}=\sigma & \left(W ^ { (l) } \cdot \operatorname { C O N C A T } \left(h_{u}^{(l-1)},\right.\right. \\
& \left.\left.\operatorname{AGGREGATE}\left(\left\{h_{v}^{(l-1)}: v \in \mathcal{N}(u)\right\}\right)\right)\right)
\end{aligned}
\tag{1}
\end{equation*}
where $\mathcal{N}(u)$ denotes the neighbors of node $u, W^{(l)}$ is a learnable weight matrix, and $\sigma$ is a non-linear activation function.
